title: Montezuma Castle National Monument: Places
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     History & Culture     Places               Places       Montezuma Castle National Monument preserves dwellings built by the Southern Sinagua culture between 1100 and 1425 CE.  Above you'll find a link to view the list of both prehistoric and historic structures that can be found here. Below you'll find photo galleries of the structures themselves. Explore and enjoy!
